begin_memory_text: Some small talk, stuff about weather and career choice
middle_memory_text: More about what I do as a job and what she does
end_memory_text: She was talking a lot about her job, which I found very interesting
rest_of_day_open: Okay, I have a decent amount of work to do unfortnately though. So it will probably be a little stressful, but certainly I have had bigger issues in my life and I know I can get through this. I have stuff to look foward to after this week though, which is good.
critical_positive: She was friendly and just in general had a really interesting job that I enjoyed hearing about. I have done some of these conversations before, and she definitely had the most interesting career and was honest about it. We also are both in science and love animals, so we had that in common and it was easy to find questions to ask her.
critical_negative: I though overall it was pretty good, I get a little nervous talking to new people and I do think that showed a little. I may have asked too many questions too, because I was genuinely interested in her career. I tried to not invade her privacy though or ask anything inappropriate.

begin_memory_text: we awkwardly said hello and did the typical name/occupation/location drop. we talked about the weather in our respective locations and talked a bit about teleworking versus normal working conditions.
middle_memory_text: we moved on to talking about her PhD program and how far along and how well that was going. we discussed pets and how living conditions affect the ability to keep pets (such small vs large dogs). there was also discussion about higher education and the differences in going into graduate programs without any breaks versus taking a break to work full time and then coming back to school.
end_memory_text: we mostly talked about my job - as a scientist she was interested in my work as a lab animal vet...the species i work with (i mostly talked about monkeys), the agents, COVID protocol work, etc.
rest_of_day_open: i am going to be swamped at work and dreading having to come in this weekend for protocol support. i will talk to other vets at work that were gone most of the week and update them on clinical cases they missed and any progress on protocol support they're involved with. i would like to exercise tomorrow evening, but i will likely be too tired and end up exercising on saturday.
critical_positive: we were both scientists, so that was common ground that got us speaking a bit more. ...that was probably about it? i think we were both perfectly nice and polite, but that doesn't make for conversation. curiosity in the other's discipline also worked well, but that just expands upon us being scientists.
critical_negative: we're both awkward. there was a lot of obvious and internalized head nodding and looking away from the camera and slightly too long pauses. because we were awkward the conversation took a bit to get going and we spoke about mundane things like the weather initially. i get the feeling that neither of us is particularly talkative.
